col1: Why doesn't hungryhead work with Internet Explorer or my browser?
col2: If you're having trouble, use latest version of [Chrome](https://www.google.com/intl/en/chrome/browser/ "Chrome Browser"), [Firefox](https://www.mozilla.org/en-GB/firefox/new/  "Firefox browser") or [Safari](http://www.apple.com/uk/safari/  "Safari browser") -- we do most of our testing in Chrome and Firefox. We also support IE11+ on windows.

col1: How do I delete my account?
col2:
To delete your account:
- [Log in](/login/ 'Login Link') to your account
- Go to the homepage
- Click on your profile image or badge in the upper right hand corner, in the dropdown select **Settings**
- Select delete account tab and, click **Delete account*
This deletes your account and your user profile. It takes about a few minutes to an hour to delete your account - depending on the content in your profile.

col1: Do you share content with search engines - Google etc.?
col2: HungryHead is a member only platform. We don't share any private data with search engines. Only people who are registered and joined can view your profiles and ideas.

col2:

col1: How can I invite my team members?
col2:
You can invite your team members by clicking on the **+** icon at the top right of the members section. After creating an invite, the app sends an email to the team member. 
Your team member can then click on the link sent in the email and join your idea.

col1: How can I collaborate with my idea team members?
col2: Everyone in the team has access to the idea in private mode. You can chat and update your idea profile in realtime.

col1: How can I change my profile settings?
col2: Click on your profile icon on top right of the menu and then go to settings.

col1: How do you handle privacy and security?
col2: Hungryhead is a private community and therefore, we don't share your content with search engines or third-party services.
